{
  "metadata": {
    "name": "Romanian phoneme inventory",
    "notes": "Core contrasts: seven oral vowels and the standard consonant set p b t d k ɡ t͡s t͡ʃ d͡ʒ f v s z ʃ ʒ h m n l r. The semivowels j and w are included as optional segmental objects for tautosyllabic vocoid sequences. Romanian palatalization, assibilation, S-palatalization, and /o/ ~ /o̯a/ alternations are treated as alternation facts rather than automatic additions to the core contrastive inventory. Velars /k ɡ/ bear DORSAL but are unspecified (0) for the tongue-body features High/Low/Front/Back/Round, which are reserved for the dorsal vocoids; this keeps [DORSAL] on [-syllabic] segments = velar and on [+syllabic] segments = back/high vowel. Tense is left unspecified (0) on the vowels, as Romanian is not described with a tense/lax contrast in this inventory."
  },
